        "title": "The generic passive: Suomes juodaan",
        "summary": "When it's about people in general, Finnish drops the subject and uses the passive: Suomes juodaan paljon kahvii = in Finland people drink a lot of coffee. The same form covers habits (kesäl grillataan), rules of a place, and how-questions (miten tää lausutaan?).",
